name: Ammonium hydroxide
safety_guideline:
Absorbed into the body by inhalation of its vapor or aerosol and by ingestion. Corrosive to the eyes,
 the skin and the respiratory tract. Corrosive on ingestion as well. Inhalation of high concentration 
vapor may cause laryngeal oedema, inflammation of the respiratory tract, and pneumonia. 
The effects may be delayed. Lungs may be affected by prolonged exposure to vapor or aerosol. 
Very toxic to aquatic organisms.
